text: The Strand Theatre in Jennings, Louisiana, at 432 N. Main St., was built in 1939. It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1998. It is a Moderne-style building designed by architects Favrot, Reed, and Fred. It was the only theatre open in Jennings during most of 1939 to 1948.
